text: Ah! More witless, craptastic, "Van Helsing"/"I, Frankenstein"-style bullshit. This time, with big, bald, monosyllabic Vin Diesel. And also Michael Caine, who likely only agreed to be in this sucktacular epic in exchange for great flipping wodges of cash, and as long as they kept him liberally plied with good scotch (see rocks glass in trailer). The most aggressively *stoopid* thing about this movie, though, is that its heroes are a bunch of delusional religious zealots who go around killing "witches," which is exactly what a bunch of delusional religious zealots are doing right now, in Kenya and Tanzania. Fantasy or not, there are few things more vile or despicable than exploiting this kind of superstitious idiocy and ignorance for the sake of a buck. You go, Vin, with your bad, witch-killing self. I used to kind of like you, but now you just suck, man. (If anyone's interested, do a Google image search for "witch killings" in Kenya and Tanzania. But only if you have a strong stomach...)

How many rape victims were burned at stake just because rapist told that he was under spell? How many young women were murdered because some jealous wife told a priest that she charmed her husband? How many elderly, harmless ladies were killed because they gave herbs to sick children? How many mathematicians for using Arab numbers?
